  "text": "The SVD analysis and the comparison of eigenarrays between two datasets were performed essentially as previously described [CITATION_1] . Briefly, SVD was performed separately on matrices M, A, resulting in matrices u M (2786 × 5), m genes common between these two datasets. This resulted in matrices u MA and u AM . We calculated the Pearson correlation coefficient r between each pair of columns of u MA and u AM . The two-sided p-values corresponding to these correlations were obtained from the Student t distribution, with the t statistics calculated with the formula t = r[d /(1-r",
